<TITLE> National unity needed: Khaleda </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Mar 05 (bdnews24.com)  Leader of the opposition Khaleda Zia has said "national unity" will see the nation through the aftermath of the BDR mutiny. British high commissioner Stephen Evans met with the BNP chairperson and former prime minister at her Gulshan office on Thursday evening. Her adviser Shamsher Mobin Chowdhury told reporters that the British envoy conveyed the distress and condolence of the British government over the bloody BDR mutiny of Feb 25-26. "Khaleda Zia told the high commissioner that our country was facing great trouble after the mutiny, but that we can overcome this difficulty through national unity," said the adviser. She reiterated once again that the opposition was always ready to help the government in this crisis, said Chowdhury. bd
